Assistance to Disabled Persons for Purchase/Fitting of Aids and Appliances (ADIP Scheme): Objective: Provide assistive devices to enhance mobility and functionality of PwDs. Benefits: Financial assistance for purchasing aids like hearing devices, prosthetics, and mobility equipment. Eligibility: Individuals with at least 40% disability and a monthly income not exceeding â‚¹20,000. Implementing Body: Ministry of Social Justice and Empowerment.
Deendayal Disabled Rehabilitation Scheme (DDRS): Objective: Support voluntary organizations in providing services to PwDs. Benefits: Grants-in-aid for projects related to education, vocational training, and rehabilitation. Eligibility: Registered organizations working in the disability sector. Implementing Body: Ministry of Social Justice and Empowerment.
National Fund for Persons with Disabilities: Objective: Offer financial assistance for various needs of PwDs. Benefits: Support for education, vocational training, and medical treatment. Eligibility: PwDs and organizations working for their welfare. Implementing Body: Department of Empowerment of Persons with Disabilities.
Chief Minister's Comprehensive Health Insurance Scheme (Tamil Nadu): Objective: Provide health insurance coverage to economically vulnerable groups, including PwDs. Benefits: Coverage for various medical treatments and surgeries. Eligibility: Residents of Tamil Nadu with an annual income below a specified threshold. Implementing Body: Government of Tamil Nadu.
Scholarship Schemes for Students with Disabilities: Objective: Promote education among students with disabilities. Benefits: Financial assistance for pursuing primary to higher education. Eligibility: Students with at least 40% disability and a parental income below a specified limit. Implementing Body: Ministry of Social Justice and Empowerment.
